@0 = ~SHADOWDANCER: Shadowdancers move with effortless grace along the threshold between light and darkness, weaving shadows and illusion into their art. They are a varied lot, but all see shadow as a force to shape rather than fear. Whether driven by curiosity, ambition, or necessity, shadowdancers are renowned for their stealth, agility, and ability to strike swiftly from the dark. Their talents make them exceptional scouts and spies, able to infiltrate and gather information with a skill few thieves can match. Despite their affinity with darkness, they are not necessarily evil; to a shadowdancer, darkness is simply a tool, stripped of the moral judgments others place upon it.

Advantages:
– Permanent Infravision and immunity to magical darkness.
– Stealthy: +20 points to Hide in Shadows and Move Silently at level 1, improving by +5 every 3 levels thereafter.
– Natural Evasion: +2 Armor Class, +1 bonus to Movement Rate and all Saving Throws.
– Slippery Mind: A shadowdancer's mind is difficult to pin down, gaining a +2 bonus to Saving Throws vs. all Enchantment and Illusion effects. Additionally, every round, <PRO_HESHE> has a 50% chance per round to be freed of a negative mind-influencing effect if <PRO_HESHE> succeeds at a Save vs. Breath at -4. The chances to make an attempt increase by 10% at level 8 and every eighth level thereafter, up 100% chances at level 40.
– Hide In Plain Sight: Once per turn, <PRO_HESHE> can hide for 20 seconds even while observed with a chance of success that depends on <PRO_HISHER> Hide in Shadows skill. Cooldown decreases by 1 round at level 5 and every 5 levels thereafter, to a minimum of 2 rounds.
– May cast Shadowstep once per day, gaining one additional use every two levels thereafter.

SHADOWSTEP: The first variation of this ability, Planeshift, allows the shadowdancer to step into the Shadow Plane for about 7 seconds, moving faster, effectively resisting and dodging every attack, and becoming completely undetectable while time stands still for everyone else. During this time, <PRO_HESHE> cannot harm others, be targeted, or cast spells, but may move freely. Upon returning to the Prime Material Plane, <PRO_HESHE> gains brief temporary bonuses to <PRO_HISHER> combat ability, including the power to backstab from any angle. These benefits scale with the shadowdancer's level. As an alternative to Planeshift, <PRO_HESHE> may instead Blink, that is, instantly teleport to a visible location.

– May cast Shadow Leap once per turn.

SHADOW LEAP: This lesser version of Shadowstep lets the shadowdancer slide through the shadows faster than the eye can follow, teleporting a short distance and gaining mild bonuses for one round. 

– At level 3, <PRO_HESHE> may cast Shadow Call once per day.

SHADOW CALL: This skill allows the shadowdancer to draw energy from the Demiplane of Shadow to create semi-real versions of various spells. At level 3, <PRO_HESHE> gets access to Shadow Illusion and Sleep. At level 6, <PRO_HESHE> gains access to Invisibility, Magic Missile, and Blindness. At level 12, <PRO_HESHE> gains access to Darkness 15' Radius, Melf's Acid Arrow, and Minor Globe of Invulnerability. Finally, at level 18, <PRO_HESHE> gains access to Shadow Fireball and Shadow Door. Where applicable, these spells are cast at half <PRO_HISHER> current level.

– At level 4, <PRO_HISHER> may cast Summon Shadow once per day.

SUMMON SHADOW: Bring forth an undead shadow from the Demiplane of Shadow for 8 hours. It is loyal to the caster, resistant to damage, and immune to turning and effects that banish summoned creatures. Its touch can temporarily drain Strength from its victims, and as the shadowdancer gains experience, the shadow grows as well, becoming more capable and eventually evolving into more powerful shadows.

– At level 5, the shadowdancer may cast Shadow Evade once day.

SHADOW EVADE: The shadowdancer cloaks <PRO_HIMHER>self in shadow for 5 rounds, becoming harder to hit. It grants a +4 bonus to Armor Class, a +2 bonus to all Saving Throws, and +15% universal damage resistance. During this time, <PRO_HESHE> is also invisible.

– At level 6, gains a second use of Shadow Call.
– At level 9, gains a second use of Shadow Evade and Damage resistance increases to 20%.
– At level 10, gains the passive benefit Shadow Haven.

SHADOW HAVEN: The shadowdancer becomes undetectable by all mundane and magical means except True Sight, and regenerates 1 Hit Point per round while invisible. In addition, the shadowdancer's deeper understanding of the Shadow Plane allows <PRO_HIMHER> to fight spectral creatures more effectively, gaining +2 to Armor Class, THAC0, Damage, and Saving Throws against them.

– At level 12, gains a third use of Shadow Call.
– At level 9, gains a third use of Shadow Evade and Damage resistance increases to 25%.
– At level 18, gains a fourth use of Shadow Call.

Disadvantages:
– Alignment restricted to any non-lawful
– Backstab multiplier does not progress after 4x
– May only distribute 15 skill points per level among thieving skills
– May not spend skill points on the Set Traps ability
– May not select any Thief High-Level Abilities other than Assassination and Use Any Item
– May not dual-class~

@1 = ~Inspired by your foster father's colorful tales of rogues and scoundrels, you spent your childhood yearning for a life cloaked in shadow and secrecy. While other children played at knights and dragons, you slipped unseen through Candlekeep's quiet halls, imagining yourself a phantom among the unwary. The ambling, distracted monks became secret lords and unsuspecting marks in your mind, their purses and possessions tempting small tests of your growing skill. Gorion, ever perceptive, has more than once asked you to discreetly return an inkwell or scroll to its rightful place, usually with little more than a knowing glance. Though the deeper vaults of the keep remain beyond your reach, you have found little satisfaction in pilfering from your caretakers. Your heart yearns for a larger stage, one where silence, subtlety, and a gift for moving unseen may at last find their proper use.~

@2 = ~“Where there is much light, the shadow is deep.” You never took that for wisdom, only for useful fact. Under cover of night, bright streets create blind spots, and those who watch the light seldom notice what moves between it. You learned how to cross open ground by choosing the right moment, how to vanish without a trace, and how to step from one pool of darkness into another so swiftly that witnesses swear you were never in between. That talent drew the wrong sort of attention the night a job ended with too many unanswered questions and no explanation anyone found comforting.

The city watch has little patience for mysteries, and the pious are quick to condemn anything that smacks of blasphemy or dark arts. Guild leaders, for their part, do not look kindly upon methods they cannot understand. None can prove what you have done, yet rumor and superstition have gathered thick enough around your name that it has become uncomfortable to speak aloud. In your trade, being hard to catch is useful. Being conspicuous is not.

So, with a heavy heart, you left the familiar rooftops and lamplit streets of home and made for the North. Perhaps in a few years the stories will fade and be dismissed as tavern-folly. Until then, frontier towns offer darker nights, looser scrutiny, more room to work, and fewer witnesses inclined to fill in the gaps.~

// SHADOWDANCER SPELLS

@1100 = ~Slippery Mind: Freed from mind-influencing effect~
@300 = ~Planeshift~
@301 = ~Blink~
@3 = ~Shadowstep~
@4 = ~Shadowstep
This ability may be cast in one of two forms: Planeshift or Blink. The shadowdancer chooses the version at the moment of casting; if no choice is made, the spell is lost.

Planeshift: Instantly step into the Shadow Plane for about 7 seconds, increasing movement speed by a factor of 2 (+1 every 3 levels). While in the Shadow Plane, the shadowdancer is completely undetectable, immune to all effects that allow a Saving Throw, and time stands still for others. During this period, <PRO_HESHE> cannot attack, be attacked, or cast spells, but may move freely for tactical positioning.

Upon returning to the Prime Material Plane, the shadowdancer gains the following benefits for about half a round:

– May backstab once from any direction
– Attacks cannot critically miss and ignore weapon speed factor
– Luck: +1
– THAC0: +1, with an additional +1 every 3 levels (up to +6)
– Damage: +1, with an additional +1 every 6 levels (up to +3)
– Critical Hit Chance: +5%, improving to +10% at level 13 and +15% at level 25

The offensive benefits are consumed after the first successful attack that is not blocked by weapon immunities. Additionally, for one round, the shadowdancer will also remain invisible and under the effects of Blur (+3 Armor Class, +1 to Saving Throws).

Blink: Alternatively, the shadowdancer may instantly teleport to any visible location. This version grants all the same benefits as Planeshift, which apply immediately after teleporting.

This spell does not break invisibility.~

@5 = ~Shadow Illusion~
@6 = ~Shadow Illusion
The shadowdancer creates silent illusions out of raw shadow to disorient an enemy. On a failed Save vs. Spell, the target suffers fear, berserk, blindness, or confusion for 1 round (randomly).

For the next 4 rounds, it is allowed to make another Save vs. Spell each round to get rid of the effect but may still succumb in subsequent rounds. For the full 5 rounds, it also suffers 25% spell failure and loses immunity to backstabs.

The spell improves in the following manner:

– The save penalty improves by 1 at level 8 and every 6 levels thereafter, to a maximum of -4. 
– At level 12, the effect spreads to nearby enemies after the initial hit.
– At level 14, it also causes 10% physical damage vulnerability and a -4 Armor Class penalty.
– At level 17, blindness always applies independently of the other possible effects if the Save is failed.

This spell has no effect on creatures with Intelligence 18 or higher, or on those able to see through illusions. It ignores Magic Resistance and dispelling effects, though True Sight prevents and counters its effects.~

@7 = ~Summon Shadow~
@8 = ~Summon Shadow
Call forth an invisible undead shadow from the Demiplane of Shadow for 8 hours, or until it is slain. The creature cannot be blinded and possesses the usual immunities of a spectral undead being, but cannot be turned or destroyed by banishment effects. It is resistant to damage, regenerates slowly—especially while invisible—and can temporarily drain Strength from its victims with a touch if they fail a Save vs. Death.

This loyal undead companion is weaker than its natural counterparts, but grows stronger as the shadowdancer gains experience. It evolves into more powerful and resilient forms, gains innate abilities, and ultimately becomes a greater kind of shadow:

– Shadow from levels 4 to 11
– Greater Shadow from levels 12 to 19
– Shadowlord from levels 20 to 27
– Greater Shadowlord from level 28 onward

The creature's Hit Dice are always 1 lower than the shadowdancer's, up to a maximum of 27 HD. Note that no more than one of these creatures may be active at a time.~

@700000 = ~Summon Nighthaunt~
@700001 = ~Summon Nighthaunt
Permanently upgrade your shadow summon, gaining the ability to call forth a nighthaunt from the Demiplane of Shadow instead. This powerful nightshade is tougher and far deadlier. The nighthaunt's abilities and statistics improve slightly at shadowdancer levels 35 and 40.

Requirements: Level 30 or higher, Shadowdancer only~

@700002 = ~Summon Nighthaunt
Call forth an invisible nighthaunt from the Demiplane of Shadow for 8 hours, or until it is slain. This powerful nigthshade possesses all the immunities of lesser shadows, but is stronger, more resistant to damage, and can occasionally drain one or two levels with its attacks. It becomes slightly more powerful at shadowdancer levels 35 and 40.~

@700010 = ~You may not summon more than one shadowdancer shade.~

@9 = ~Hide in Plain Sight~
@90 = ~Failed to Hide in Plain Sight~
@10 = ~Hide in Plain Sight
Immediately hide, even in plain sight, for 20 seconds. This ability has a base cooldown of 1 turn, and the cooldown decreases by 1 round at level 5 and every 5 levels thereafter, reaching a minimum of 2 rounds at level 40.

The chance of success is tied to the shadowdancer's Hide in Shadows skill, as follows:

– 0-30: 50% chance of success
– 31-50: 65% chance of success
– 51-75: 80% chance of success
– 76-100: 90% chance of success
– 101-150: 95% chance of success
– 151-200: 99% chance of success
– 201+: 100% chance of success

Note that this chance is affected by penalties or bonuses to Hide in Shadows, such as from magical effects or gear.~

@10010 = ~Hide in Plain Sight is available for use.~

@11 = ~Shadow Form
Duration: 5 rounds + 1 round/10 levels starting at level 30
Casting Time: Instant
Area of Effect: The caster

This ability is an enhanced form of Shadow Evade that temporarily replaces part of the shadowdancer's flesh with shadowstuff, rendering <PRO_HIMHER> partially incorporeal. For its duration, the shadowdancer regenerates 1 Hit Point per second, gains +4 Armor Class, +4 to all Saving Throws, Improved Invisibility, and 50% Damage Resistance.

The shadowdancer also cannot be detected by divination spells until <PRO_HESHE> partially reveals <PRO_HIMHER>self by taking offensive actions, or until the effect ends. This does not prevent creatures that naturally see through invisibility from detecting the shadowdancer.

Requirements: Improved Shadow Evade~

@12 = ~Shadow Maze
This ability opens a temporary gateway to a small pocket of the Plane of Shadow. All enemies within 7 feet of the shadowdancer must make a Save vs. Spell at a -4 penalty or become trapped inside that space for 5 to 14 rounds. This spell becomes harder to resist as the shadowdancer grows more experienced: the penalty becomes -5 at level 28 and -6 at level 36.~

@13 = ~One With The Shadow~
@14 = ~One With The Shadow
The shadowdancer's deep communion with Shadow grants <PRO_HIMHER> the following permanent benefits:

– Immunity to blindness
– Casting speed, movement rate, and weapon speed factor are permanently increased by 2
– Backstabs can be performed from any angle
– Critical Hit Effect: On a critical hit, the target loses immunity to backstabs for 2 rounds, if it had such immunity. For the same duration, the shadowdancer gains +5% critical hit chance and immunity to critical misses. These bonuses do not stack, but further critical hits refresh their duration.

Requirements: Shadowdancer only~

@130 = ~Fell Strike~
@131 = ~Fell Strike
The shadowdancer may infuse <PRO_HISHER> attacks with energy from the Shadow Deep. For 1 round after activation, <PRO_HISHER> attacks deal maximum damage. For 1 turn, <PRO_HISHER> backstabs also gain one of the following effects, chosen when this ability is activated:

– Veiled Strike: Each backstab has a 30% chance to render the shadowdancer immediately invisible for 2 rounds. Additionally, it blinds the target for 4 rounds unless a Save vs. Spell at -4 succeeds. If the target is blinded already, the chances for the shadowdancer to become invisible on backstab are 60% instead.

– Chilling Strike: Each backstab deals an extra 1d6+1 cold damage and 1d6+1 magic damage. This bonus damage is doubled against blinded targets. In addition, each backstab has a 20% chance to force the target to make a Save vs. Death (at -2 if blinded). On a failed save, the target is stunned for 1 round 20% of the time; otherwise, the target is slowed for 2 rounds.

– Enervating Strike: Each backstab forces the target to make a Save vs. Death at -2 or have <PRO_HISHER> Strength and movement rate halved for 8 rounds. If the target is already enervated, the backstab instead imposes a -5 penalty to THAC0, a -2 penalty to Armor Class, a -1 penalty to Saving Throws, and causes the target to deal minimum damage with physical attacks. These secondary effects end when the enervation expires.

During this time, the shadowdancer's critical hit chance is increased by 5%. In addition, if the target is immune to backstabs, each successful hit (backstab or not) has a 10% chance to remove that immunity for 10 seconds. This can occur only once every 5 rounds per target. These effects ignore Magic Resistance. Fell Strike's variations do not stack; each new application replaces the previous one.

Requirements: Shadebound~

@13100 = ~Backstab Immunity Stripped~

@132 = ~Veiled Strike~
@133 = ~Chilling Strike~
@134 = ~Enervating Strike~

@15 = ~Self-Concealment~
@16 = ~Self-Concealment
Your essence merges further with shadow, granting a permanent +%zs_sd_selfconcealment_dr%% resistance to all damage types and a +1 bonus to Armor Class. This ability can be selected up to three times.

Requirements: Shadowdancer only~

@2100 = ~Shadow Call~
@2101 = ~Shadow Call
This skill allows the shadowdancer to draw energy from the Demiplane of Shadow to create a semi-real duplicate of a selection of spells, cast at half <PRO_HISHER> level.

At level 3, the following spells are available:

SHADOW ILLUSION: Conjures shadowy illusions to disorient an enemy. On a failed Save vs. Spell, the target suffers fear, berserk, blindness, or confusion for 1 round. For the next 4 rounds, it gets a new save each round, but may still succumb. For 5 rounds, it also suffers 25% spell failure and loses immunity to backstabs. The save penalty improves by 1 at level 8 and every 6 levels thereafter, to a maximum of -4. At level 12, the effect spreads to nearby enemies. At level 14, it also causes 10% physical damage vulnerability and a -4 Armor Class penalty. At level 17, blindness always applies. This spell has no effect on creatures with Intelligence 18 or higher, or on those able to see through illusions. It ignores Magic Resistance and dispelling effects, though True Sight prevents its effects.
SLEEP: Lull all creatures in a 15-ft. area of effect around the point of impact into a comatose slumber. Targets with more than 4 HD are unaffected.

From level 6, the following spells are available:

BLINDNESS: Temporarily blinds the target for 2 hours if a Saving Throw is failed, and imposes a -4 penalty to attack rolls and Armor Class.
INVISIBILITY: Become completely invisible for 24 hours, as per the arcane spell of the same name.
MAGIC MISSILE: Conjure illusory magic missiles that unerringly strike the target, dealing 1d4+1 magic damage each. Every four levels, the shadowdancer adds one extra missile to the spell, up to 5 missiles.

At level 12, the following spells become available:

MELF'S ACID ARROW: Conjure a magical arrow that speeds unerringly to its target. The arrow inflicts 2d4 points of acid damage, and for every 6 levels of the shadowdancer, the acid lasts for another round, unless somehow dispelled, inflicting another 2d4 points of damage each round.
MINOR GLOBE OF INVULNERABILITY: Creates a faintly shimmering magical sphere around the shadowdancer that prevents any 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell effects from penetrating. It lasts for 1 round per 2 levels of the shadowdancer.
DARKNESS 15' FEET: Pull a mass of magical darkness over a 15-ft. area, blinding anyone inside as long as they remain there. After leaving the area, the victim may remain blinded for up to 1 round.

Finally, at level 18, the following spells are gained:

SHADOW FIREBALL: An illusory version of Fireball that deals a mix of fire, cold, and magic damage in a purple blast. It otherwise functions identically. The shadowdancer and <PRO_HISHER> summoned shade are immune to <PRO_HISHER> own Shadow Fireball.
SHADOW DOOR: By means of this spell, the shadowdancer creates the illusion of a door and appears to step through it and disappear. In reality, <PRO_HESHE> darts aside and can flee, totally invisible (as per the Improved Invisibility spell), for 9 rounds plus 1 round every 2 levels of the shadowdancer.~

@21050 = ~Shadow Fireball~

@2107 = ~Umbral Call~
@2108 = ~Umbral Call
This skill allows the shadowdancer to upgrade <PRO_HISHER> Shadow Call capabilities in order to cast even more spells at half <PRO_HISHER> level. This will also add one more use of Shadow Call. The following spells are added to <PRO_HISHER> pool of spells:

DELAYED BLAST SHADOW FIREBALL: An illusory version of Delayed Blast Fireball that deals a combination of 15d6 fire, cold, and magic damage in a purple blast. It otherwise functions identically. The shadowdancer and <PRO_HISHER> summoned shade are immune to <PRO_HISHER> own Delayed Blast Shadow Fireball. This replaces the Shadow Fireball ability.

SHADOW SHIELD: For 2 turns, the shadowdancer is cloaked in a mantle of shifting shadows that blocks the first 3 physical attacks, grants Blur, and creates 8 shadowy mirror images. It also grants immunity to necromancy, level drain, and instant-death effects, as well as a +20 bonus to Hide in Shadows and Move Silently. This spell can be dispelled by Dispel Magic, but not by True Sight.

MASS INVISIBILITY: Upon casting this spell, the shadowdancer causes all friendly creatures within the area of effect to be affected by the spell Improved Invisibility. This replaces the Shadow Door ability and is cast with a casting speed of 1.

Requirements: Shadowdancer only~

@21080 = ~Delayed Blast Shadow Fireball~

@21090 = ~Umbral Call
This skill allows the shadowdancer to draw substantial energy from the Demiplane of Shadow to conjure a semi-real duplicate of a selection of spells, cast at half <PRO_HISHER> level. The following abilities are available:

SHADOW ILLUSION: Conjures shadowy illusions to disorient an enemy. On a failed Save vs. Spell, the target suffers fear, berserk, blindness, or confusion for 1 round. For the next 4 rounds, it gets a new save each round, but may still succumb. For 5 rounds, it also suffers 25% spell failure and loses immunity to backstabs. The save penalty improves by 1 at level 8 and every 6 levels thereafter, to a maximum of -4. At level 12, the effect spreads to nearby enemies. At level 14, it also causes 10% physical damage vulnerability and a -4 Armor Class penalty. At level 17, blindness always applies. This spell has no effect on creatures with Intelligence 18 or higher, or on those able to see through illusions. It ignores Magic Resistance and dispelling effects, though True Sight prevents its effects.

SLEEP: Lull all creatures in a 15-ft. area of effect around the point of impact into a comatose slumber. Targets with more than 4 HD are unaffected.

BLINDNESS: Temporarily blinds the target for 2 hours if a Saving Throw is failed, and imposes a -4 penalty to attack rolls and Armor Class.

INVISIBILITY: Become completely invisible for 24 hours, as per the arcane spell of the same name.

MAGIC MISSILE: Conjure illusory magic missiles that unerringly strike the target, dealing 1d4+1 magic damage each. Every four levels, the shadowdancer adds one extra missile to the spell, up to 5 missiles.

MELF'S ACID ARROW: Conjure a magical arrow that speeds unerringly to its target. The arrow inflicts 2d4 points of acid damage, and for every 6 levels of the shadowdancer, the acid lasts for another round, unless somehow dispelled, inflicting another 2d4 points of damage each round.

MINOR GLOBE OF INVULNERABILITY: Creates a faintly shimmering magical sphere around the shadowdancer that prevents any 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell effects from penetrating. It lasts for 1 round per 2 levels of the shadowdancer.

DARKNESS 15' FEET: Pull a mass of magical darkness over a 15-ft. area, blinding anyone inside as long as they remain there. After leaving the area, the victim may remain blinded for up to 1 round.

DELAYED BLAST SHADOW FIREBALL: An illusory version of Delayed Blast Fireball that deals a combination of 15d6 fire, cold, and magic damage in a purple blast. It otherwise functions identically. The shadowdancer and <PRO_HISHER> summoned shade are immune to <PRO_HISHER> own Delayed Blast Shadow Fireball.

SHADOW SHIELD: For 2 turns, the shadowdancer is cloaked in a mantle of shifting shadows that blocks the first 3 physical attacks, grants Blur, and creates 8 shadowy mirror images. It also grants immunity to necromancy, level drain, and instant-death effects, as well as a +20 bonus to Hide in Shadows and Move Silently. This spell can be dispelled by Dispel Magic, but not by True Sight.

MASS INVISIBILITY: Upon casting this spell, the shadowdancer instantly causes all friendly creatures within the area of effect to be affected by the spell Improved Invisibility.~

@2109 = ~Shadow Shield~

@2120 = ~Shadow Dance~
@2121 = ~Shadow Dance
For 5 rounds, the shadowdancer performs an agile and disorienting dance that allows <PRO_HIMHER> to automatically evade spells and special attacks that can normally be dodged, such as dragon breath, fireballs, lightning bolts, skull traps, explosives, and similar effects.

During this time, the shadowdancer becomes invisible for 3 seconds once each round, disrupting enemy targeting unless they can see through invisibility. Armor Class is improved by 6, Saving Throws by 3, and Movement Rate by 4 (base 9). In addition, the shadowdancer moves so swiftly that missile attacks cannot hit <PRO_HIMHER>.

This ability cannot be dispelled or removed by Breach, although the invisibility effect itself can still be removed by True Sight and other effects that dispel invisibility.~

@2122 = ~Shadow Dance: Evaded effect~

@23 = ~Backstab Immunity removed~
@24 = ~Backstab Immunity removal effect wore off~

@25 = ~Shadow Evade~
@26 = ~Shadow Evade
For 5 rounds, the shadowdancer cloaks <PRO_HIMHER>self in shadow, becoming harder to hit. While this effect lasts, <PRO_HESHE> gains +4 Armor Class, +2 to all Saving Throws, 15% Damage Resistance, and invisibility. Damage Resistance increase by 5% at levels 15 and 20. Shadow Evade also grants immunity to Shadow Fireball and Delayed Blast Shadow Fireball when cast through Shadow Call.~

@27 = ~Improved Shadow Evade~
@28 = ~Improved Shadow Evade
The shadowdancer's Shadow Evade ability is permanently upgraded to Shadow Form. In this enhanced form, Damage Resistance increases to 50%, invisibility becomes Improved Invisibility, the shadowdancer regenerates 1 Hit Point per second, and gains immunity to all divination spells for the duration of the effect.

Requirements: Shadowdancer only~

@60 = ~Shadow Twin
Once per day, the shadowdancer may create an almost exact duplicate of themselves for 2 turns. The duplicate is created at 60% of the their current level and has all the abilities they would have at that level. It also has 60% of their Hit Points. The duplicate is fully under the shadowdancer's control. The Shadow Twin cannot create a Shadow Twin themselves, or use the Summon Shadow or Summon Nighthaunt abilities.

Requirements: Shadowdancer only~

@70 = ~Shadow Leap~
@71 = ~Shadow Leap
Step through the shadows, teleporting a short distance. Unlike Shadowstep, this ability requires concentration, but may be used at will once per turn and does not break invisibility. The following benefits apply for 1 round:

– THAC0: +1
– Armor Class: +1
– Saving Throws: +1
– Weapon Speed Factor: -3

These bonuses do not stack with themselves or with those granted by Shadowstep. The entire effect is consumed on the first successful attack made against an enemy, if such an attack is made before the round ends.~

@7100 = ~Shadow Leap is available for use~

// END OF SHADOWDANCER SPELLS

// SUMMON SHADOW DIALOG
@100 = ~Your shadowy companion slowly turns to look at you with its formless eyes. A cold, emotionless voice rings clearly in your mind: "Greetings, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. What is it you command?"~
@101 = ~Attack enemies as soon as you see them.~
@102 = ~Do not attack enemies unless they attack you first.~
@103 = ~Do not attack enemies unless they attack me first.~
@104 = ~Do not attack or react in any way, only follow my direct orders.~
@105 = ~Actually, what you're doing right now is fine, carry on.~
@106 = ~Your shadowy companion slowly turns to look at you with its formless eyes and stares at you, awaiting orders. A voice says in your mind: "Yes, my <PRO_LADYLORD>?"~
@107 = ~The voice says: "As you say, my <PRO_LADYLORD>".~ // order
// @108 = ~The shade ignores your attempts to communicate with it.~ // no way of detecting "owner" for now
// END SUMMON SHADOW DIALOG

// SUMMONED SHADOW STR
@198 = ~Shadow Fade~
@199 = ~Shadow Fade
This ability allows the shade to vanish from sight. The shade can instantly become invisible for 24 hours, and the effect cannot be interrupted. Upon reaching level 16, the shade also gains the option to use Improved Invisibility instead, which lasts for 2 turns.~

@200 = ~Fade~
@201 = ~Fade
The shade instantly becomes invisible for 24 hours. This effect cannot be interrupted.~

@202 = ~Drain Life~
@203 = ~Drain Life
The shade drains the life of the victim, causing 1d4+4 magic damage, which is transferred to the shade for 1 turn as healing or extra health.~

@204 = ~Vampiric Touch~
@205 = ~Vampiric Touch
The shade drains health from the victim as per the Vampiric Touch spell.~

@206 = ~Teleport Without Error~
@207 = ~Teleport Without Error
The shade teleports to any point within its field of vision instantly and becomes invisible for 1 round.~

@208 = ~Beshadowed Form~
@209 = ~Beshadowed Form
The shade envelops itself in shadowstuff, greatly increasing its defenses for 2 rounds. While this effect is active, it gains +4 Armor Class, +50% Fire Resistance, and +50% Magic Damage Resistance. In addition, all of its other pre-existing resistances are increased by 50% of their current value. The shade also becomes invisible as per Improved Invisibility and regenerates 1 Hit Point per second.

From level 16 onward, this ability also blocks the first successful melee or ranged attack that would inflict physical damage, so long as it occurs within 4 rounds of activation.

This ability may be used once every 2 turns. The cooldown is reduced to 15 rounds at level 15, 13 rounds at level 19, and 10 rounds at level 24.~

@20209 = ~Beshadowed Form is available for use.~

@210 = ~Darkness, 15' radius~
@211 = ~Darkness, 15' radius
The shade causes total, impenetrable darkness. Neither normal nor magical light works in the area of effect. All vision (including infravision) is severely limited; any hostile creature caught in the area is, for all practical purposes, blinded as per the 1st-level wizard spell. Creatures that leave the area regain normal vision after 1 round.~

@212 = ~Deep Fade~
@213 = ~Deep Fade
The shade becomes invisible as per the Improved Invisibility spell for 2 turns.~

@214 = ~Dispel Magic~
@215 = ~Dispel Magic
The shade attempts to dispel all magic as per the Dispel Magic spell.~

@216 = ~Doom the Living~
@217 = ~Doom the Living
The nighthaunt points at a living target and releases a ray of dark energy. The target must make a Save vs. Death at -2 or be slain instantly. If the save succeeds, the target still takes 1d10+4 magic damage and is afflicted with the effects of the Doom spell for 1 turn. This secondary Doom effect cannot be resisted by saving throws.~

@218 = ~See Invisibility~
@219 = ~See Invisibility
The shade briefly gains the ability to see invisible creatures, revealing them unless they are protected from divination. This spell is cast instantly as a free action once every 3 rounds and cannot be interrupted.~

@220 = ~Umbral Swap~
@221 = ~Umbral Swap
The shade instantly swaps places with an allied creature through a Shadowstep. The ally becomes invisible for 2 rounds and immediately stops attacking. The shade appears at the ally's former location, ready to fight, and gains the following benefits for 2 rounds:

– Armor Class: +2
– Saving Throws: +2
– THAC0: +2
– Damage: +2
– Damage Resistance: +5%
– Critical Hit Chance: +5%
– Attacks per Round: +1/2

This ability may be used once every 2 turns and has no effect if used on a non-ally or on the shade itself. Its cooldown is reduced each time the shade evolves into a stronger form, to a minimum of 5 rounds if it eventually becomes a Nighthaunt.~

@22200 = ~Umbral Swap is available for use.~

@22500 = ~Shadebound~
@22501 = ~Shadebound
The shadowdancer's command over the energies from the Plane of Shadow strengthens <PRO_HIMHER> in battle while under the effects of <PRO_HISHER> shadow arts.

While under the effects of Shadow Evade or Shadow Form:

– Movement rate: +1
– Magic Resistance: +10%
– Damage Resistance: +3%
– Retributive Invisibility: When struck, the shadowdancer has a 5% chance to immediately re-enter Shadow Evade or Shadow Form (this may occur only once every 3 rounds), lashing out at the attacker for 2d6 points of magic damage and stunning them for 1 round. A Save vs. Spell at -1 halves the damage and negates the stun.

While under the effects of Shadowstep or Shadow Leap:

– Movement rate: +1
– Damage: +2
– THAC0: +2
– Critical Hit Chance: +5%

Requirements: Shadowdancer only~

