// ITMS
@5000 = ~This rod seems to writhe and shift in your hand, yet you feel no movement. Oily shadows constantly crawl across its surface, though their source is a mystery. The rod exudes a dark aura, and when gripped in the proper way, it allows the wielder to seemingly "jump" between locations in battle.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
– Shadowstep 3 times/day, cast at character level
  Special: Step through the shadows as per the shadowdancer ability of the same name, gaining offensive benefits that allow to strike harder, and defensive benefits that allow you to evade almost any effect for a very brief time.

Weight: 2~

// OTHER TWEAKS
@6000 = ~Spirit Form
Duration: 5 rounds + 1/10 levels starting at level 30
Casting Time: Instant
Area of Effect: The caster

The shaman slips into a space between the spirit world and the material plane, becoming partially incorporeal. For its duration, the shaman regenerates 1 Hit Point per second, gains +4 Armor Class, +4 to all Saving Throws, Improved Invisibility, and 50% Damage Resistance.

The shaman also cannot be detected by divination spells until <PRO_HESHE> partially reveals <PRO_HIMHER>self by taking offensive actions, or until the effect ends. This does not prevent creatures that naturally see through invisibility from detecting the shaman.~

